Git Add Remote Repo

$   mkdir <dir_name>
$   cd <dir_name>
$   mkdir src
$   git init
$   git remote add origin <ssh_url_from_git_hub>
$   git pull

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Docker Command

$   docker-compose up --build -d
$   docker-compose down

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Install larval

mkdir src (host machine)

$   docker-compose exec php-apache /bin/bash
$   composer create-project laravel/laravel=8.* .

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tailwind css

Follow this url: https://tailwindcss.com/docs/guides/laravel

Inside Docker working Dir (/var/www/laravel_docker)

$   npm install (don't need to run npm install, if docker already installed)

$   npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
$   npx tailwindcss init

Update webpack.mix.js file, add tailwindcss as a PostCSS plugin.

    mix.js("resources/js/app.js", "public/js")
      .postCss("resources/css/app.css", "public/css", [
        require("tailwindcss"),
      ]);

Add the paths to all of your template files in your tailwind.config.js file.

    module.exports = {
      content: [
        "./resources/**/*.blade.php",
        "./resources/**/*.js",
        "./resources/**/*.vue",
      ],
      theme: {
        extend: {},
      },
      plugins: [],
    }

Add the @tailwind directives for each of Tailwindâ€™s layers to your ./resources/css/app.css file.

    @tailwind base;
    @tailwind components;
    @tailwind utilities;

Run your build process with npm run watch.

$npm run watch

Need to add css link to HTML Header block
example:

    <head>
      <meta charset="utf-8">
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
      <link href="{{ asset('css/app.css') }}" rel="stylesheet">
    </head>

